@startuml seq-content-page-streaming
'' ============================================================================
'' vinary-viewer - Sequence: bounded content previews for logs, tables, and archives
''
'' PlantUML over Mermaid because: this flow has two separate IPC phases, a
'' reusable main-process parser service, archive recursion, and finite page
'' lookahead/lookbehind. PlantUML sequence diagrams keep those actors explicit
'' while preserving the same color legend used by the rest of the suite.
'' ============================================================================
!include _vv-theme.iuml

title Bounded preview streaming - first page, adjacent page, nested archive

autonumber "0:"

actor User #white
participant "reagent UI\ncontent-view" as UI RENDERER_TINT
participant "preload\nwindow.vv" as Vv IPC_TINT
participant "main.service\nipcMain" as Svc MAIN_TINT
participant "content_service.js\nparser/streamer" as CS MAIN_TINT
participant "Archive reader\nyauzl/tar-stream" as AR FS_TINT
participant "Filesystem\nReadable stream" as FS FS_TINT
participant "DataScript\ncontent cache" as DS DATASCRIPT_TINT

== first open ==
User -> UI : open `/var/log/app.log`\nor `bundle.zip`
UI -> Vv : `vv:open(path)`
Vv -> Svc : **vv:open**
activate Svc
Svc -> CS : `openUri(path)`
activate CS

alt large log or delimited text
  CS -> FS : create bounded read stream
  FS --> CS : lines/rows until page 0 + lookahead
  CS --> Svc : `{kind, paged:true, page}`
else archive URI or archive file
  CS -> AR : list current archive layer\nor open selected member
  AR --> CS : immediate children\nor entry stream
  CS --> Svc : `{kind:"archive", entries}`\nor first preview page
else office/workbook preview
  CS -> FS : read capped preview bytes
  FS --> CS : bounded buffer
  CS --> Svc : `{kind:"office"|"table", html|sheets}`
end

Svc -> Vv : **vv:content** bounded payload
deactivate CS
deactivate Svc
Vv -> UI : `onContent`
UI -> DS : `[:content/received payload]`
UI -> UI : render table/log/archive preview

== adjacent page ==
User -> UI : Next page
UI -> Vv : `contentPage({path, kind, page:n})`
Vv -> Svc : **vv:content-page**
activate Svc
Svc -> CS : `contentPage(request)`
activate CS
CS -> FS : stream from source start\ncollect only requested page
FS --> CS : page n + one lookahead row/line
CS --> Svc : `{index, rows|lines, hasPrev, hasNext}`
deactivate CS
deactivate Svc
Svc --> Vv : bounded page
Vv --> UI : Promise resolves
UI -> UI : cache page n and prefetch n-1/n+1

== nested archive ==
User -> UI : open `outer.zip!/inner.tar.gz!/logs/app.log`
UI -> Vv : `vv:open(vv-archive://...?chain=...)`
Vv -> Svc : **vv:open**
Svc -> CS : parse virtual archive chain
CS -> AR : open each archive layer\nup to depth limit
AR --> CS : final member stream
CS -> FS : stream final log/table preview
FS --> CS : bounded first page
CS --> Svc : preview payload
Svc -> Vv : **vv:content**
Vv -> UI : render final member

legend right
  |= Colour |= Concept |
  |<#3A5BA0>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;| MAIN / Node IO |
  |<#2D9574>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;| Renderer / UI |
  |<#B1951D>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;| IPC seam |
  |<#A45BAD>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;| DataScript content cache |
  |<#9F8766>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;| filesystem / archive stream |
endlegend
@enduml
